Description: Frontal, half-length portrait of Egyptian adult female carrying young child on shoulder. Female wearing gown, black crepe veil decorated with coins, metal nose cylinder. Child unclothed. Albumen print. Format: Mounted on card, second print on other side of card.
Curator's comments: Nose cylinder known as "arous u-urqu" [?]. J M Hudson, 1/12/1997. Biography: Other images in series inscribed McCarthy, relationship with images unclear.
